718010f-a.title: Manhattan: Canal Street - Baxter Street
718010f-a.text:
Canal Street, west from Baxter Street. At the left is
the junction formed by Walker Street. The Grand Street
Ferry street car is shown thereupon. Across the view,
in the center runs Centre Street. The horse drawn car
on the right is north bound on this thoroughfare. In
the vague background is the North (Hudson) River and it's
Jersey shore. A view similar to this appears in Valen-
tines Manual of 1863.
About 1860
American Studio, photo
87 Nassau St., N.Y.C.
Gift of Urbrock Collection
